snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a maker enrolled in my local community in Mallorca, Spain. We coordinate through a Telegram channel and a Google Doc spreadsheet where you inform of the number of items you have produced and if you are in need of material, and there's a couple of people that are in touch with the public health service, so they determine what is needed, and where. We are in almost total lockdown, so a few volunteers are allowed to collect items from maker's homes and send them to authorities, who desinfect them and send them to hospitals, local health services and whoever needs them.
We ask for no money. All we ask is that is you can, donate some plastic filament.

And It makes us proud to contribute.

We will get through this together (but isolated by the moment).

snippet.textDisplay: With some people having to pay $30,000+ for treatments I’m not sure why we need to help by donating masks (or anything) to hospitals.... If they want the nation to donate paid resources, they need to be donating treatment to the sick. I work in a field where face masks are necessary for our health on a daily basis, and we can no longer get face masks yet we are an “essential” service..... I’m not knocking this because you guys are doing a good thing, but in your case that’s easy to do. You’ve got the money. For us who don’t, it’s a safer bet to keep the mask on our face and protect ourselves and our families rather than donating to a hospital that will charge us through the roof if we need treatment.

We’ve gotten a relatively mild one, now. Let’s hope we’ll be prepared much better for the real deal which could happen within this century, if we’re unlucky the next decades.
